<article>
    <h1>AU&#xAD;GUST BERG X MOR&#xAD;RIS &amp; CO</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201009/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-10-09"><time>2020-10-09</time></a>
        - <span>STYLE LIFE</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Lo­cally founded Dan­ish watch brand Au­gust Berg has an un­likely col­lab­o­ra­tor: cen­turies-old Bri­tish fur­nish­ing house Mor­ris & Co.</p>
    <p>The lat­ter was founded in 1861 by artist and tex­tile de­signer Wil­liam Mor­ris, who is of­ten cred­ited as a ma­jor player in the Bri­tish Arts and Crafts Move­ment. His de­signs are sold to­day un­der li­cence on wall­pa­pers and fab­rics.</p>
    <p>For this, a se­lec­tion of Mor­ris &</p>
    <p>Co’s pop­u­lar prints and tex­tures are fea­tured on the watch di­als – mak­ing this the her­itage brand’s first time­piece col­lec­tion.</p>
    <p>On why a fur­nish­ing brand was cho­sen, Au­gust Berg founder An­ders Peter Juel Sauer­berg tells The Straits Times: “Wil­liam Mor­ris was mo­ti­vated to pro­vide af­ford­able art for all, which is a per­fect match with Au­gust Berg’s fo­cus on ac­ces­si­ble lux­ury.”</p>
    <p>Prices start at $289.</p>


